snippet.description:
https://www.moddb.com/mods/eshq

ESHQ is a GoldSr/HL1 mod made by Russian dev team RD_AAOW, using HL1 assets and Xash3D, it also uses its own software, so don’t download it on Steam (you will erase the original « hl.exe » from valve) but in your common Program Files folder.

Not set in HL universe, you’re a gov. spy sent on a mission at Evil Scientists HeadQuarters (ESHQ) set in fictional town « Bernier City », to steal some secret files… and a 20 hour long journey into the unknown, begins.

I collected 420 documents (they serve as « clues » to hidden containers) and several hidden containers supposed to unlock abilities but it’s still unavailable (so it's just for glory, for the moment).

@00:00 1. Welcome to ESHQ

We collect some intel and weapons in the building, and encounter « Sampi » ϡ (Gman model), a mysterious guy who knows some dark secrets about your mission.

@23:35 2. Run, spy, run!

We leave ESHQ to an hotel, a metro station, kills some HECU/militaries to protect the « evil » scientists, and on Sampi ϡ' s advice, broadcasts all secret files to the public/media through ES comm center.

@55:28 : 3. End of ESHQ

Comm center collapses under air strikes sent to kill the player/leak of media, we flee to ES sea labs.

@01:08:44 4. 'We got him!'

The player is caught by militaries, stripped of weapons, beaten, but escapes after more air strikes destroy the sea labs, then reach and turn off a ship, which drifts and collides with underwater part of the Bernier city zoo; large volume of mutagenic liquid reaches city canalization.

@01:33:08 5. Radiocity

Zombies and alien fauna spreads around the city, we reach the biological research center where we finally find some friendly Barneys and scientists.


@01:56:15 6. Two-front war

We move through deenergized metro tunnels and fights crowds of zombies, militaries, and contacts Sampi ϡ with a transmitter, after that we go to city hospital and car service, and finally a railway depot that has been used for evacuation.

@03:02:03 7. Unsuccessful set of circumstances

We reach « Base 5 », weapon-focused center, but it is largely affected by earthquakes, making us travel through lava, et… We escape through a large ship where we encounter the bad guy, unnamed scientist (Gordon Freeman model), who flees when the ship breaks down, as well as « base 5 ». 

@03:41:55 8. The way back

The ship falls down to an old mining complex, we finally reach an old train which crashes near « base 4 », advanced virtual reality-focused center.


@04:26:20 9. The ordeal

Bad Gordon sends us through VR test chambers, levels based on Mario Bros !! until the engines break down. After that, we reach a giant rocket silo which we launch on Bernier City, in turn completly obliterated, after that we flee to underground caves.

@05:10:44 10. Ghost town

We wander through the destroyed city and fights with burned but still walking mutants, then we encounter in an hidden lab, « GHOST », a supercomputer gone rogue who killed every lab humans. We destroy it before finding a friendly ship in the stadium, meeting Sampi ϡ again who sets up the next mission : going to Bernier Mountain to kill Bad Gordon, after taking some rest, ammo and HP.


@05:55:58 11. Dead peak

We go through the moutain inside and outside before reaching « Base 3 », a weather control-focused center. We meet again Bad Gordon this time with his own boss (a white-suited Gman), an experiment takes place but goes wrong and blows everyone to bits – minus the hero. 

@06:34:06 12. Is anybody live here?

We go downside the moutain and find the old Bernier village, a hidden path with a labyrinth leads to « Base 2 «, abandoned alien fauna-focused center filled with headcrabs and even a Gonarch, it leads to « base 1 », aquabiology-focused center.

@07:10:32  13. Unreliability

We flood « base 1 » to reach the surface and meets again Sampi ϡ  who congratulates us before trying to kill us for « knowing too much », but the pink nebula from « base 3 » failed experiment strike again and forces Sampi ϡ to flee. We go back to « base 3 » through some villages, empty asylums and city transport paths, before finding an advanced teleport system.

